            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EEzekiel%20reminds%20us%20that%20it%20is%20not%20the%20way%20people%20start%20in%20their%20walks%20with%20God%2C%20but%20the%20way%20they%20finish%2C%20that%20counts.%20When%20a%20righteous%20man%20turns%20from%20his%20righteousness%20and%20commits%20sin%2C%20the%20righteous%20things%20he%20has%20done%20are%20no%20longer%20remembered.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESitting%20back%20and%20resting%20on%20our%20spiritual%20laurels%20is%20a%20dangerous%20posture.%20How%20often%20have%20people%20served%20the%20Lord%20for%20perhaps%20a%20year%2C%20five%20years%2C%20ten%20years%2C%20or%20longer%20.%20.%20.%20and%20then%2C%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20their%20lives%2C%20thrown%20it%20all%20away%3F%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EMoses%20spent%20forty%20years%20in%20the%20wilderness%20being%20faithful%20in%20God's%20house%20(Numbers%2012%3A7).%20However%2C%20at%20the%20very%20end%20of%20the%20journey%2C%20he%20lost%20his%20composure%20in%20front%20of%20all%20Israel.%20%22Rash%20words%20came%20from%20Moses'%20lips%22%20and%20%22trouble%20came%20to%20Moses%20because%20of%20them%22%20(Psalm%20106%3A33%2C%2032%20NIV).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20there%20are%20people%20who%20spend%20their%20lives%20in%20wickedness%20but%20repent%20in%20the%20end%2C%20%22All%20their%20past%20sins%20will%20be%20forgotten%2C%20and%20they%20will%20live%20because%20of%20the%20righteous%20things%20they%20have%20done%22%20(Ezekiel%2018%3A22).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDon't%20be%20self-satisfied%2C%20thinking%20you%20cannot%20fall%2C%20and%20don't%20condemn%20yourself%2C%20believing%20you%20cannot%20rise.%20Remain%20in%20an%20attitude%20of%20repentance%2C%20and%20you%20will%20make%20it%20to%20the%20end.%20%22Put%20all%20your%20rebellion%20behind%20you%2C%20and%20get%20for%20yourselves%20a%20new%20heart%20and%20a%20new%20spirit.%20For%20why%20should%20you%20die%2C%20O%20people%20of%20Israel%3F%20I%20don't%20want%20you%20to%20die%2C%20says%20the%20Sovereign%20Lord.%20Turn%20back%20and%20live!%22%20(Ezekiel%2018%3A31-32).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
